00:00:52.720 --> 00:00:58.560
Merritocracy is the key point and I like&nbsp;
that Musk started to talk about meritocracy&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:58.560 --> 00:01:04.480
recently. So you can see that like people are&nbsp;
on the similar mindset and meritocracy for&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:04.480 --> 00:01:09.200
example in Singapore means something a little bit&nbsp;
different than a corporate structure when it comes&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:09.200 --> 00:01:14.000
to governance like people are rewarded really&nbsp;
for their service to government and they don't&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:14.000 --> 00:01:19.040
evaluate it with shares but in Singapore there&nbsp;
is also this strong notion of meritocracy but&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:19.040 --> 00:01:23.600
liberal and meritocracy is something different&nbsp;
it's really inviting these corporate elements&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:23.600 --> 00:01:29.600
into the organization of the society while we&nbsp;
are also democracy because we let the majority&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:29.600 --> 00:01:34.880
of citizens to veto any rule or even person&nbsp;
in the government that they don't like. But&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:34.880 --> 00:01:39.440
we don't give the democracy the option to rob&nbsp;
other people. We don't give the democratic&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:39.440 --> 00:01:44.880
element the the option to make the decisions&nbsp;
on behalf of minority. It must be the majority&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:44.880 --> 00:01:50.080
not of citizens but of the shareholders or of&nbsp;
the shares that make decisions in Liberland.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:50.080 --> 00:01:59.920
